TPM_PT_PCR_SAVE - PCR is saved and restored by TPM_SU_STATE
TPM_PT_PCR_EXTEND_L0 - PCR may be extended from locality 0
TPM_PT_PCR_RESET_L0 - PCR may be reset by TPM2_PCR_Reset() from locality 0
TPM_PT_PCR_EXTEND_L1 - PCR may be extended from locality 1
TPM_PT_PCR_RESET_L1 - PCR may be reset by TPM2_PCR_Reset() from locality 1
TPM_PT_PCR_EXTEND_L2 - PCR may be extended from locality 2
TPM_PT_PCR_RESET_L2 - PCR may be reset by TPM2_PCR_Reset() from locality 2
TPM_PT_PCR_EXTEND_L3 - PCR may be extended from locality 3
TPM_PT_PCR_RESET_L3 - PCR may be reset by TPM2_PCR_Reset() from locality 3
TPM_PT_PCR_EXTEND_L4 - PCR may be extended from locality 4
TPM_PT_PCR_RESET_L4 - PCR may be reset by TPM2_PCR_Reset() from locality 4
TPM_PT_PCR_NO_INCREMENT - modifications to this PCR (reset or Extend) will not increment the pcrUpdateCounter
TPM_PT_PCR_DRTM_RESET - PCR is reset by a DRTM event
TPM_PT_PCR_POLICY - PCR is controlled by policy
TPM_PT_PCR_AUTH - PCR is controlled by an authorization value
TPM_PT_FAMILY_INDICATOR - a 4-octet character string containing the TPM Family value (TPM_SPEC_FAMILY)
TPM_PT_LEVEL - the level of the specification
TPM_PT_DAY_OF_YEAR - the specification day of year using TCG calendar
TPM_PT_YEAR - the specification year using the CE
TPM_PT_MANUFACTURER - the vendor ID unique to each TPM manufacturer
TPM_PT_VENDOR_STRING_1 - the first four characters of the vendor ID string
TPM_PT_VENDOR_STRING_2 - the second four characters of the vendor ID string
TPM_PT_VENDOR_STRING_3 - the third four characters of the vendor ID string
TPM_PT_VENDOR_STRING_4 - the fourth four characters of the vendor ID sting
TPM_PT_VENDOR_TPM_TYPE - vendor-defined value indicating the TPM model
TPM_PT_FIRMWARE_VERSION_1 - the most-significant 32 bits of a TPM vendor-specific value indicating the version number of the firmware
TPM_PT_FIRMWARE_VERSION_2 - the least-significant 32 bits of a TPM vendor-specific value indicating the version number of the firmware
TPM_PT_INPUT_BUFFER - the maximum size of a parameter (typically, a TPM2B_MAX_BUFFER)
TPM_PT_HR_TRANSIENT_MIN - the minimum number of transient objects that can be held in TPM RAM
TPM_PT_HR_PERSISTENT_MIN - the minimum number of persistent objects that can be held in TPM NV memory
TPM_PT_HR_LOADED_MIN - the minimum number of authorization sessions that can be held in TPM RAM
TPM_PT_ACTIVE_SESSIONS_MAX - the number of authorization sessions that may be active at a time
TPM_PT_PCR_COUNT - the number of PCR implemented
TPM_PT_PCR_SELECT_MIN - the minimum number of octets in a TPMS_PCR_SELECT.sizeOfSelect
TPM_PT_CONTEXT_GAP_MAX - the maximum allowed difference (unsigned) between the contextID values of two saved session contexts
TPM_PT_NV_COUNTERS_MAX - the maximum number of NV Indexes that are allowed to have the TPMA_NV_COUNTER attribute SET
TPM_PT_NV_INDEX_MAX - the maximum size of an NV Index data area
TPM_PT_MEMORY - a TPMA_MEMORY indicating the memory management method for the TPM
TPM_PT_CLOCK_UPDATE - interval, in milliseconds, between updates to the copy of TPMS_CLOCK_INFO.clock in NV
TPM_PT_CONTEXT_HASH - the algorithm used for the integrity HMAC on saved contexts and for hashing the fuData of TPM2_FirmwareRead()
TPM_PT_CONTEXT_SYM - TPM_ALG_ID, the algorithm used for encryption of saved contexts
TPM_PT_CONTEXT_SYM_SIZE - TPM_KEY_BITS, the size of the key used for encryption of saved contexts
TPM_PT_ORDERLY_COUNT - the modulus - 1 of the count for NV update of an orderly counter
TPM_PT_MAX_COMMAND_SIZE - the maximum value for commandSize in a command
TPM_PT_MAX_RESPONSE_SIZE - the maximum value for responseSize in a response
TPM_PT_MAX_DIGEST - the maximum size of a digest that can be produced by the TPM
TPM_PT_MAX_OBJECT_CONTEXT - the maximum size of an object context that will be returned by TPM2_ContextSave
TPM_PT_MAX_SESSION_CONTEXT - the maximum size of a session context that will be returned by TPM2_ContextSave
TPM_PT_PS_FAMILY_INDICATOR - platform-specific family (a TPM_PS value)(see Table 24)
TPM_PT_PS_LEVEL - the level of the platform-specific specification
TPM_PT_PS_REVISION - the specification Revision times 100 for the platform-specific specification
TPM_PT_PS_DAY_OF_YEAR - the platform-specific specification day of year using TCG calendar
TPM_PT_PS_YEAR - the platform-specific specification year using the CE
TPM_PT_SPLIT_MAX - the number of split signing operations supported by the TPM
TPM_PT_TOTAL_COMMANDS - total number of commands implemented in the TPM
TPM_PT_LIBRARY_COMMANDS - number of commands from the TPM library that are implemented
TPM_PT_VENDOR_COMMANDS - number of vendor commands that are implemented
TPM_PT_NV_BUFFER_MAX - the maximum data size in one NV write command
TPM_PT_MODES - a TPMA_MODES value, indicating that the TPM is designed for these modes
TPM_PT_MAX_CAP_BUFFER - the maximum size of a TPMS_CAPABILITY_DATA structure returned in TPM2_GetCapability
TPM_PT_HR_NV_INDEX - the number of NV Indexes currently defined
TPM_PT_HR_LOADED - the number of authorization sessions currently loaded into TPM RAM
TPM_PT_HR_LOADED_AVAIL - the number of additional authorization sessions, of any type, that could be loaded into TPM RAM
TPM_PT_HR_ACTIVE - the number of active authorization sessions currently being tracked by the TPM
TPM_PT_HR_ACTIVE_AVAIL - the number of additional authorization sessions, of any type, that could be created
TPM_PT_HR_TRANSIENT_AVAIL - estimate of the number of additional transient objects that could be loaded into TPM RAM
TPM_PT_HR_PERSISTENT - the number of persistent objects currently loaded into TPM NV memory
TPM_PT_HR_PERSISTENT_AVAIL - the number of additional persistent objects that could be loaded into NV memory
TPM_PT_NV_COUNTERS - the number of defined NV Indexes that have NV TPMA_NV_COUNTER attribute SET
TPM_PT_NV_COUNTERS_AVAIL - the number of additional NV Indexes that can be defined with their TPMA_NV_COUNTER and TPMA_NV_ORDERLY attribute SET
TPM_PT_ALGORITHM_SET - code that limits the algorithms that may be used with the TPM
TPM_PT_LOADED_CURVES - the number of loaded ECC curves
TPM_PT_LOCKOUT_COUNTER - the current value of the lockout counter (failedTries)
TPM_PT_MAX_AUTH_FAIL - the number of authorization failures before DA lockout is invoked
TPM_PT_LOCKOUT_INTERVAL - the number of seconds before the value reported by TPM_PT_LOCKOUT_COUNTER is decremented
TPM_PT_LOCKOUT_RECOVERY - the number of seconds after a lockoutAuth failure before use of lockoutAuth may be attempted again
TPM_PT_NV_WRITE_RECOVERY - number of milliseconds before the TPM will accept another command that will modify NV
TPM_PT_AUDIT_COUNTER_0 - the high-order 32 bits of the command audit counter
TPM_PT_AUDIT_COUNTER_1 - the low-order 32 bits of the command audit counter
